":true,"ts_fgc_i":true,"ts_it":true,"ts_fs":13.0,"ts_ff":"Droid Serif","ts_it_i":false,"ts_bgc":"#c5e1a5","ts_fs_i":false,"ts_bgc_i":false}},{"ty":"as","st":"text","si":8297,"ei":8310,"sm":{"ts_ff_i":false,"ts_un":false,"ts_fgc":"#757575","ts_un_i":true,"ts_fgc_i":false,"ts_fs":11.0,"ts_ff":"Roboto","ts_fs_i":false}},{"ty":"as","st":"text","si":8329,"ei":8988,"sm":{"ts_ff_i":false,"ts_un":false,"ts_fgc":"#000000","ts_un_i":true,"ts_fgc_i":true,"ts_it":true,"ts_fs":13.0,"ts_ff":"Droid Serif","ts_it_i":false,"ts_bgc":"#fde096","ts_fs_i":false,"ts_bgc_i":false}},{"ty":"as","st":"text","si":8989,"ei":9002,"sm":{"ts_ff_i":false,"ts_un":false,"ts_fgc":"#757575","ts_un_i":true,"ts_fgc_i":false,"ts_fs":11.0,"ts_ff":"Roboto","ts_fs_i":false}}]; DOCS_modelChunkLoadStart = new Date().getTime(); _getTimingInstance().incrementTime(, DOCS_modelChunkLoadStart - DOCS_modelChunkParseStart); DOCS_warmStartDocumentLoader.loadModelChunk(DOCS_modelChunk); DOCS_modelChunk = undefined;</script><script type="text/javascript" nonce="/3Dt1z2GOz/kM8/Yrb1Kk69kR/I"  nonce="/3Dt1z2GOz/kM8/Yrb1Kk69kR/I">DOCS_modelChunkParseStart = new Date().getTime();</script><script type="text/javascript" nonce="/3Dt1z2GOz/kM8/Yrb1Kk69kR/I"  nonce="/3Dt1z2GOz/kM8/Yrb1Kk69kR/I">DOCS_modelChunk = [{"ty":"is","ibi":9009,"s":"\n\n\u0010\u0012\u001c\n\u0010\u0012\u001c*\n\u001cBecause it helps break logjams, whether created by disagreement, fear, procrastination, or lethargy, and whether created by external obstacles or internal ones, the question “Couldn’t\n\nMay 10, 2017\n\u001c54\n\u0011\n\u0011\n\n\u0010\u0012\u001c\n\u0010\u0012\u001c*\n\u001cwe at least . . . ?” sparks movement.\n\nMay 10, 2017\n\u001c54\n\u0011\n\u0011\n\n\n4.   How Can I Help?\n\n\u0010\u0012\u001c\n\u0010\u0012\u001c*\n\u001cWhile this is a genuine problem, we should not let the real pitfalls of the savior complex extinguish one of the most humane instincts there is—the instinct to lend a hand. The trick is to help others without believing yourself to be, or acting like you are, their savior.\n\nMay 10, 2017\n\u001c56\n\u0011\n\u0011\n\n\u0010\u0012\u001c\n\u0010\u0012\u001c*\n\u001cAll of which is to say that how you help matters just as much as that you do help, which is why it is essential to begin by asking, “How can I help?” If you start with this question, you are asking, with humility, for direction. You are recognizing that others are experts in their own lives, and you are affording them the opportunity to remain in charge, even if you are providing some help.\n\nMay 10, 2017\n\u001c56\n\u0011\n\u0011\n\n\u0010\u0012\u001c\n\u0010\u0012\u001c*\n\u001cBy asking her how they could help, she explained, they were allowing her to retain her independence and dignity. In addition to showing respect, asking how you can help is also—not surprisingly—likely to make your assistance more effective. My wife, Katie, asks this question, and pays attention to the answer, as well as anyone I know\n\nMay 10, 2017\n\u001c57\n\u0011\n\u0011\n\n\u0010\u0012\u001c\n\u0010\u0012\u001c*\n\u001cPatrick ultimately received asylum, and he went on to find a good job in New Jersey and create a new life. A few years later, Patrick asked me to serve as the best man at his wedding. The memory of his wedding still brings tears to my eyes. When I later asked him why he wanted me to be his best man, he said, “Because you were my first friend here. You listened to me.”\n\nThis might be good for edvestment platform\n\nMay 10, 2017\n\u001c61\n\u0011\n\u0011\n\n\u0010\u0012\u001c\n\u0010\u0012\u001c*\n\u001cnudging others to identify, express, and confront their own problems. This is sometimes understandably hard to do, as Atul Gawande describes movingly in Being Mortal , in which he recounts the difficult choices advanced cancer patients must make about their own care. Because facing your own mortality is indescribably difficult, and because doctors naturally want to save patients, it is hard for doctors and patients to have candid discussions about the end of life. But as Gawande points out, cancer patients and their families most need someone to help guide them with candor and compassion. It occurred to me when reading this book that if doctors asked the patients how they could help, before simply pointing out all of the various interventions they could perform, they would in a way force the question, which only the patient can answer: What do you want to do? How do you want to spend what may be your last months of life? How do you want to make that decision—what information would be useful, for example, and who else would you like to include in the conversation?\n\nMay 10, 2017\n\u001c61\n\u0011\n\u0011\n\n\u0010\u0012\u001c\n\u0010\u0012\u001c*\n\u001chelp them and, if so, how. More often than not, they eventually tell me that I can’t really do anything. But in saying this they are already starting to figure out the problem for themselves. What they most needed to do was vent, get some sympathy, and figure out a solution for themselves. The need to vent is not confined to kids. My cousin Tracy, who is as funny as she is wise, told me a story once of coming home after a really frustrating day at work and recounting her day to her boyfriend. Instead of listening to the entire story, her boyfriend immediately started offering ideas about what she could have done to solve her problems. She found this maddening. “I didn’t want him to solve my problems,” she told me. “I just wanted him to listen and understand that I had a crappy day at work.”\n\nMay 10, 2017\n\u001c63\n\u0011\n\u0011\n\n\u0010\u0012\u001c\n\u0010\u0012\u001c*\n\u001cIf you ask friends, family members, or colleagues how you can help, you are not offering to solve their problems with specific suggestions. Instead, you are validating that they have a real problem and letting them know you are available to help, if need be. You are showing both sympathy and empathy, which is sometimes all someone needs. Put differently, in asking how you can help, sometimes you already have.\n\nMay 10, 2017\n\u001c64\n\u0011\n\u0011"},{"ty":"te","id":"i.19","spi":9018},{"ty":"te","id":"i.20","spi":9235},{"ty":"te","id":"i.21","spi":9329},{"ty":"te","id":"i.22","spi":9635},{"ty":"te","id":"i.23","spi":10062},{"ty":"te","id":"i.24","spi":10431},{"ty":"te","id":"i.25","spi":10879},{"ty":"te","id":"i.26","spi":11992},{"ty":"te","id":"i.27","spi":12827},{"ty":"as","st":"paragraph","si":9009,"ei":9009,"sm":{"ps_klt_i":true,"ps_sb_i":true,"ps_awao_i":true,"ps_ls":1.0,"ps_sa_i":true,"ps_sm_i":true,"ps_kwn_i":true,"ps_ifl_i":true,"ps_ls_i":true,"ps_il_i":true,"ps_ir_i":true,"ps_al_i":true}},{"ty":"as","st":"paragraph","si":9010,"ei":9010,"sm":{"ps_klt_i":true,"ps_sb_i":true,"ps_awao_i":true,"ps_ls":1.0,"ps_sa_i":true,"ps_sm_i":true,"ps_kwn_i":true,"ps_ifl_i":true,"ps_ls_i":true,"ps_il_i":true,"ps_ir_i":true,"ps_al_i":true}},{"ty":"as","st":"tbl","si":9011,"ei":9011,"sm":{"tbls_cols":{"cv":{"op":"set","opValue":[{"col_wv":468.0,"col_wt":0}]}},"tbls_bw":0.75,"tbls_bc":"#bdbdbd"}},{"ty":"as","st":"cell","si":9013,"ei":9013,"sm":{"cell_pb_i":false,"cell_pr_i":false,"cell_pt_i":false,"cell_pt":0.0,"cell_pb":0.0,"cell_pr":0.0,"cell_pl_i":false,"cell_pl":0.0}},{"ty":"as","st":"tbl","si":9015,"ei":9015,"sm":{"tbls_cols":{"cv":{"op":"set","opValue":[{"col_wv":54.0,"col_wt":0},{"col_wv":358.5,"col_wt":0},{"col_wv":54.0,"col_wt":0}]}},"tbls_bw":0.0}},{"ty":"as","st":"cell","si":9017,"ei":9017,"sm":{"cell_pr_i":false,"cell_bl":{},"cell_pt_i":false,"cell_bb_i":false,"cell_pt":0.0,"cell_bt":{},"cell_pb":0.0,"cell_pl_i":false,"cell_br":{},"cell_pb_i":false,"cell_bl_i":false,"cell_br_i":false,"cell_pr":0.0,"cell_bt_i":false,"cell_bb":{},"cell_pl":0.0}},{"ty":"as","st":"paragraph","si":9019,"ei":9019,"sm":{"ps_klt_i":true,"ps_awao_i":true,"ps_ls":1.0,"ps_sm_i":true,"ps_ls_i":true,"ps_il_i":true,"ps_ir_i":true,"ps_al_i":false,"ps_sb_i":true,"ps_sa_i":true,"ps_kwn_i":true,"ps_al":1,"ps_ifl_i":true}},{"ty":"as","st":"cell","si":9020,"